 that depicts their highly syncretistic tradition and provides a colorful window through which to examine the dynamics of religious acculturation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aCrypto-ChristianszJapan. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh1 aWhelan, Christal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhelan, Christal, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Hawaii Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000z978311056415040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082486160540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824861605423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780824861605/original  a978-3-11-056415-0  University of Hawaii Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK